A '''spasm''' is a suden, involuntary contraction of a [[musle]], a group of musles, or a hollow [[Organ (anatomy)|organ]], or a simillarly sudden [[contraction]] of an [[orifice]].  A spasm is usually acompanied by a sudden burst of [[pain]]

By extension, a spasm is also a sudden and temporary burst of [[energy]], [[activity]], or [[emotion]].

See also [[cramp]], [[angina]].

